{
  "text": "By the previous proposition, Theorem 1.1 is reduced to the problem of finding suitable mild gaps of f \u2113,\u2113 . In this section we present a proposition that provides \"many\" mild gaps of a prescribed type. This result is proved via an elementary technique known as the Maier matrix method [CITATION_1] . We require the following definition: for every m \u2208 Z and M \u2208 N + let",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "116934026"
